items.title: 2,000-year-old statue found dumped near garbage cans
items.description: Experts say the headless statue is from the Hellenistic period (between 323 and 31 BC), according to police.

items.title: Prince Harry settles lawsuit against Rupert Murdoch's U.K. News Group
items.description: Prince Harry has settled his lawsuit against Rupert Murdoch's British News Group Newspapers for an apology and "substantial damages."

items.title: Cat mistakenly left on a plane, takes 3 trips covering 4,500 miles
items.description: A Maine coon cat named Mittens made three trips in 24 hours between New Zealand and Australia.

items.title: Stay off the Charles River ice, even in the bitter cold. Here's why.
items.description: People have been trying to walk across the icy Charles River in Boston. Massachusetts State Police say it's just not safe.

items.title: Patriots safety Jabrill Peppers' trial expected to start today
items.description: New England Patriots safety Jabrill Peppers is scheduled to go on trial Wednesday in Quincy, Massachusetts on domestic violence charges.
